team11.core.agent

Class Team11Agent

  • java.lang.Object
    • team11.core.agent.Team11Agent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public abstract class Team11Agent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable

    This is an abstract Angry Birds AI agent which provides the basic framework for various implementations of AI's to play the Angry Birds game. Implementation note; do not call super() in any implementing class constructors as there are no constructors for this abstract class.

    Usage and Implementation:

    Required method(s) to implement in a super class:
    • doTurn(Vision)

    Optional methods that can be implemented in a super class:

    • onLost()
    • onWin()

    Additional helper methods for outputs:

    • error(String)
    • debug(String)
    • log(String)
    Author:
    Chris N. Hartley (cnhartle@calpoly.edu)
    See Also:
    Runnable

      • MAX_LEVEL

        public static final int MAX_LEVEL
        Specification of the maximum level for this implementation of the agent to play to. Once the MAX_LEVEL is reached, the agent will start back from level 1 and continue playing.

      • run

        public final void run()
        The run method is called to start the agent and connect it to the server to begin playing the game. This should loop continuously as long as the AI is playing the game, checking the game state.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        See Also:
        Runnable.run()

      • doTurn

        protected abstract java.util.List<Shot> doTurn(Vision vision)
        This method is used to provide the AI implementation for each turn, time to fire a bird at some target, that returns a List of Shots to fire. If there are no shots that can be taken, this must return a List with size 0.
        Parameters:
        vision - the Vision of the current level for the game.
        Returns:
        the List of Shots to fire.
        See Also:
        Shot, Vision

      • onWin

        public void onWin()
        This method is called once the score has been fully counted when the agent successfully completes a level and after the log has been appended to. This method maybe overridden by a super class to perform custom implementations on winning a level.

      • onLost

        public void onLost()
        This method is called when the agent fails to complete a level and before the level is attempted again. This method maybe overridden by a super class to perform custom implementations on losing a level.
